The GitHub repository mentioned in the post is: https://github.com/LeCoupa/awesome-cheatsheets
Use Cases:
This repository provides a collection of cheatsheets for various programming languages, frameworks, and development tools. These cheatsheets can be used to quickly reference key concepts, syntax, and best practices. They are particularly useful for:
 * Learning new technologies: Cheatsheets can help you get up to speed quickly on a new language or framework.
 * Refresher courses: If you haven't used a particular technology in a while, a cheatsheet can help you refresh your memory.
 * Debugging code: Cheatsheets can help you identify and fix errors in your code.
 * Preparing for interviews: Cheatsheets can be a valuable tool for preparing for technical interviews.
